<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="499" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,351,702]" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,567,593]" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Froehlich" authorityYear="2007" box="[322,580,567,593]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="499" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="payagua">
<emphasis box="[322,580,567,593]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">Anacroneuria payagua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described in 
<collectingRegion box="[900,1184,567,594]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">Mato Grosso do Sul state</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Froehlich, C. G." box="[1199,1376,567,593]" pageId="12" pageNumber="499" pagination="15 - 24" refId="ref8929" refString="Froehlich, C. G. (2007) Three new species of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from State of Mato Grosso do Sul, Brazil. Zootaxa, 1461 (1), 15 - 24. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1461.1.2" type="journal article" year="2007">Froehlich 2007</bibRefCitation>
), and the present study now expands its distribution to Central 
<collectingCountry box="[782,854,603,629]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The species was collected at Serra dos Pireneus and this is a new record for 
<collectingRegion box="[423,551,639,666]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
. The penial armature of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Froehlich" authorityYear="2007" box="[830,958,639,665]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="499" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="payagua">
<emphasis box="[830,958,639,665]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="499">A. payagua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite characteristic and agrees with the original description (
